pr_title: Update the tempsense flow to the current version of OpenROAD-flow-scripts
pr_body:
This updates the tempsense flow to OpenROAD-flow-scripts commit id 1aa3fd3 (Aug 4 2022)
- I tested this update with a local installation of OpenROAD (v2.0-4526-gc525def45) and an installation in a conda environment (commit 5ca26d) from the [LiteX-hub channel](https://anaconda.org/LiteX-Hub), both successful. DRC with Magic (8.3.315) and LVS with Netgen (1.5.227) also don't produce errors in conda
- LVS with Netgen (`make netgen_lvs`) will now generate Magic .ext files in objects/.../netgen_lvs/ext and .spice files in objects/.../netgen_lvs/spice
- LEF modification for NDR is now made within the OpenROAD tool (no additional .py script) -- as mentioned in  https://openfasoc.readthedocs.io/en/latest/developers-guide.html

Some things to note:
- To see the final result in the OpenROAD GUI, go to the temp-sense-gen/flow/ directory and run `make gui_final`. You can also see intermediary steps with `make gui_floorplan`, `make gui_place` and `make gui_route`.
- The sky130hd platform dir, **common to all generators**, was also updated. Some files have changed significantly, such as `config.mk`, `fastroute.tcl`, `lef/sky130_fd_sc_hd_merged.lef`, which **WILL BREAK OTHER GENERATORS**. To keep support for generators with an older version of the flow scripts, a `backup/` folder inside the platform dir contains the older files. Such generators must be updated with this new directory path to work again (PLATFORM_DIR env variable in flow/Makefile, for example).
- The run_lvspex.sh script in `common/drc-lvs-check/` (**common to all generators**) was changed to relocate the generated .ext and .spice files in the objects dir. In the tempsense, I had to change `tools/temp-sense-gen.py` to get the correct path to the .spice file when copying it to the `work/` folder (which contains all the flow results). **THIS MAY BREAK OTHER GENERATORS**.
- The `merged_spacing.lef` file, previously used in the `cdl_parser.py` script, is not generated in the flow scripts anymore (by default). The cdl parser was thus updated not to use it (thanks @alibillalhammoud).
- This is still using `pdn.cfg` for OpenROAD's pdngen (related: #81)

For a more detailed view of what changed from the base OpenROAD-flow-scripts to OpenFASOC's tempsense generator flow, you can check the commit history in this fork: https://github.com/luccareinehr/OpenROAD-flow-scripts

Closes #73 #65

pr_title: Document temp-sense-gen flow and improve docs structure
pr_body:
The temp-sense-gen flow is documented in this file: `docs/source/flow-tempsense.rst`. It is uploaded here too: https://openfasoc-py38.readthedocs.io/en/docs-tempsense/generators.html

I also tried to take the pages that were already written in the docs and organize them more logically. So, for example, the Home page now points to the Getting Started page, which at the end points to further documentation (generator flow docs and notebook examples). Please take a look: https://openfasoc-py38.readthedocs.io/en/docs-tempsense/index.html

Finally, I moved all notebooks to the `docs/source/notebooks/` folder, as well as the `notebookFiles/` folder from #99 which gets renamed here to `aux_files/` (also changed in the nb for compatibility).

Any request or feedback is appreciated!

Closes #78

pr_title: tempsense: fix LVS, pdn.cfg -> pdn.tcl, move custom header placement to its own file
pr_body:
- Closes #109

- Closes #81

- Moves the custom placement procedure from #77 to a separate script, and automatically rotates the placed cells according to their row direction (to align correctly with VDD / GND)

- Adds an option in `customPlace_east` to allow the custom placed instances to move slightly during detailed placement, to avoid overlaps with other fixed cells (tap cells for example)

- Also addresses #97 for the temp-sense-gen (for other generators, the issue might still be valid)

pr_body:
In addition to PR #112 (**to be merged before this**), this adds the possibility to make the VIN route connect to the VIN ring in multiple points of connection.

In [config.mk](https://github.com/idea-fasoc/OpenFASOC/blob/main/openfasoc/generators/temp-sense-gen/flow/design/sky130hd/tempsense/config.mk), the `VIN_ROUTE_CONNECTION_POINTS` variable is added.

If `VIN_ROUTE_CONNECTION_POINTS = 3`, for example:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/75084099/196283939-9ce59a6d-cb87-41a3-91ee-b99c266835f1.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/75084099/196284038-459a44f2-5fb4-4c91-bb2e-7f624f73c4c1.png)
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 997529230, 'comment_body': 'What do you mean?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 10, 17, 21, 33, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'msaligane', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 997529929, 'comment_body': 'Can you explain a little more what you are doing here?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 10, 17, 21, 34, 58, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'msaligane', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 997540685, 'comment_body': 'This has to do with the route from the header cells to the VIN voltage domain. It says that the value of the env variable below (VIN_ROUTE_CONNECTION_POINTS) tells the generator how many pins should be used to connect that route to the voltage domain. More pins = less resistance

Btw should I rephrase this?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 10, 17, 21, 52, 34, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'luccareinehr', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 997545398, 'comment_body': "Of course. So, this new script `create_routable_power_net.tcl` will create a routable version of the VIN net, called r_VIN. This net is used to connect the header cells to the VIN voltage domain. The user may want to use more than one pin to make this connection, to lower the route's resistance.

So, in case he specifies to do so, the `create_routable_power_net.tcl` script creates pins called `r_VIN(0)`, `r_VIN(1)`, `r_VIN(2)` and so on, By default in OpenROAD, though, they appear in the top subckt of the CDL file, so they have to be removed for LVS to pass.

If the user wants the connection to be created with 1 pin only, then the pin is called simply r_VIN (automatically by OpenROAD), the same name of the net, and also has to be removed from the CDL file for LVS to pass (this is what was implemented before this PR).", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 10, 17, 22, 1, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'luccareinehr', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 997546886, 'comment_body': "(I'll update the comments in the code)", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 10, 17, 22, 3, 27, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'luccareinehr', 'type': 'User'}]
